    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-02T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-02T12:00:00-05:00" n="229"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d229">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.24/536: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">White</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-02T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 2, 1943—noon.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>156. Reference Department’s circular telegram dated August 31, 4 p.m.<note n="53"
                        xml:id="d229fn53">Not printed.</note> Embassy with Dowling participating
                    discussed proposed simplified export control procedure with Défly, head of
                    Country Agency, who readily accepted on behalf of Government. Moreover, he
                    expressed gratification and indicated he would be prepared to institute new
                    change with minimum of delay as soon as date and procedure fixed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
